c: 4
v: 94
t: "O you who believe, if you attack in the cause of God then make a clear declaration, and do not say to those who greet you with peace: \"You are not a believer!\" You are seeking the vanity of this world; but with God are many riches. That is how you were before, but God favoured you, so make a clear declaration. God is expert over what you do"